		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				  I've been playing EQ for about two years. I have 6 characters above level 40 and 2 above 45. That's just on one server. This new Balance issue I was so happy about and then I read what they are saying.  <br>   SK's and Paladins will not get a better bash then a warrior even though SK and paladin are the only ones that use a shield. <br>   Nerfing of evade for rogues? Great. I know there are more rogue twinks out now then ever but that is because rogues are an item based character. In other words, if you want to play a rogue...level up a necro to twink out your rogue so you can be equal to the other twinks and maybe get a group. <br>   Magicians. I admit I have not read all the posts but no talk I have seen about a root or stun or shadow step or a way to get mana back. No escapabilty and more down time then any casting class. <br>   All in all this new and &quot;final&quot; balancing issue has squished my hopes of my favorite characters to play being fixed.  <br>   I did not want to believe it at first but it seems to be true. This game is made for twinks. I've done it. Everyone I play with has done it. You are given 8 characters per server and level one high enough to make life easier for the others. It's a rule to twink...you must do it. <br>   The morale of the story is if you wish to play EQ make a necro and get to level 51. Then farm equipment for the characters you really want to play. <br>   Good job guys. Only the twinks survive! <br>  <br>   Blinded by the Light <br>     Garrett		

			</td>
		</tr>
